  "prompt": "Can foreigners move to Cuba?",
  "response": "Moving to Cuba can be challenging for foreigners. While it is possible, the process is complex and heavily regulated:\n\n1. Visa Requirements:\n- Foreigners need a valid visa to stay long-term\n- Common visa types include work, student, and family reunification visas\n- Tourist visas are relatively easy to obtain but do not allow permanent residence\n\n2. Residency Process:\n- Obtaining permanent residency is difficult\n- Typically requires marriage to a Cuban citizen, having a job offer, or investing in the country\n- Government approval is necessary\n\n3. Restrictions:\n- Cuba has strict immigration laws\n- Foreign ownership of property was historically limited\n- Recent reforms have slightly relaxed some restrictions\n\n4. Work Considerations:\n- Foreign workers need special permits\n- Many jobs are reserved for Cuban citizens\n- Foreign employment is more common in specific sectors like tourism and education\n\n5. Economic Challenges:\n- Cuba has a centrally planned economy\n- Economic conditions can be challenging for foreigners\n- Limited economic opportunities compared to many other countries\n\nForeigners interested in moving to Cuba should consult Cuban embassies or immigration lawyers for current, specific guidance, as regulations can change.",
